	<Title>
		Summer sun: Know the danger zone
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Be smart when it comes to sun protection. The sun&apos;s rays are most damaging between 10 a.m. and 2 p.m. If possible, schedule your outdoor activities for early in the morning or late in the afternoon. If you must be outdoors during these peak hours, seek shade whenever possible.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
